WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.196 --> 00:00:04.693
Demand on your CARE : Caregiver Stress

00:00:04.693 --> 00:00:08.105
Setting Boundaries that Every Caregiver Must Learn

00:00:09.303 --> 00:00:13.094
People always tell caregivers ‘Must take care of yourself’ 

00:00:13.505 --> 00:00:18.147
but it’s impossible to take care of yourself if you don’t set the boundaries. 

00:00:19.174 --> 00:00:24.992
Setting boundaries is a useful way to balance your needs with the needs of care recipient, 

00:00:25.769 --> 00:00:30.632
to set personal limits and to say ‘NO’ to requests that push those limits. 

00:00:31.804 --> 00:00:35.753
Why some caregivers are reluctant to set boundaries?

00:00:35.753 --> 00:00:38.177
Fear that others will not like you, 

00:00:38.177 --> 00:00:40.874
fear that others will be angry,

00:00:40.874 --> 00:00:43.378
often want to be a "good person",  

00:00:43.378 --> 00:00:44.921
and be afraid of scandal.

00:00:46.190 --> 00:00:50.123
Forgetting that some responsibilities should be borne by others.

00:00:50.671 --> 00:00:52.437
Self-assured.

00:00:52.821 --> 00:00:55.506
Seek appreciation to affirm oneself.

00:00:55.872 --> 00:00:58.597
Always have a mentality of giving back.

00:00:59.401 --> 00:01:01.118
Fear of losing the relationship.

00:01:01.691 --> 00:01:04.162
Does not want to face conflict.

00:01:04.995 --> 00:01:06.995
How to set the boundaries?

00:01:07.937 --> 00:01:12.812
Understand that everyone has their own responsibilities and you are not alone.

00:01:13.589 --> 00:01:15.674
Don't think of yourself as "Superman". 

00:01:15.674 --> 00:01:17.350
Understand your personal limits. 

00:01:17.350 --> 00:01:21.216
Sometimes you need to admit your incompetence and need to ask for help.

00:01:21.216 --> 00:01:24.827
Understand that not being controlled by others does not mean being unloving, 

00:01:24.827 --> 00:01:27.992
and indulgence of others is not good for them. 

00:01:28.937 --> 00:01:34.063
Everyone should have the right to personal space and respect each other.

00:01:34.063 --> 00:01:39.645
Establish boundaries and learn to say "no" to the care recipient who has over control.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:45.226
Boundaries are not permanent, adjust in due course to the circumstances.

00:01:46.251 --> 00:01:48.081
Specific method

00:01:48.081 --> 00:01:50.584
Remove 'should' frames.

00:01:50.584 --> 00:01:52.584
Don't need to be perfect in everything, 

00:01:52.584 --> 00:01:54.584
set reasonable expectations.

00:01:54.584 --> 00:01:59.553
Strengthen communication with family members and openly express your needs.

00:01:59.553 --> 00:02:05.889
Learn to let go. Build a support network with other family members and seek their help.

00:02:06.106 --> 00:02:08.140
Set life boundaries, 

00:02:08.140 --> 00:02:11.846
e.g. seek help from family members to shop twice a week, 

00:02:11.846 --> 00:02:14.070
make good use of community support.

00:02:14.070 --> 00:02:19.761
Set habit boundaries, such as going out for tea with friends once a week, 

00:02:19.761 --> 00:02:22.698
or participating in activities at a community center every day.

00:02:22.698 --> 00:02:25.829
Set time boundaries, formulate schedules, 

00:02:25.829 --> 00:02:28.568
regularly carry out daily life and handling affairs, 

00:02:28.568 --> 00:02:30.757
and set work and rest times.

00:02:30.757 --> 00:02:33.913
Seek professional assistance if necessary.

00:02:34.746 --> 00:02:39.103
Setting boundaries can help you to care yourself and avoid burnout. 

00:02:39.103 --> 00:02:41.103
Take your action now! 

